OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSchools in England given   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fguidance to avoid biased   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fteaching                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Schools in England are being reminded  
OL,6, to teach sensitive issues in a         
OL,7, non-biased way, under new guidance.    
OL,9,FIt aims to help teachers cover complex 
OL,10,Ftopics, such as the history of the     
OL,11,FBritish Empire or the                  
OL,12,FIsraeli-Palestinian conflict, without  
OL,13,Fpushing one political view over        
OL,14,Fanother.                               
OL,16,FThere is also a warning against        
OL,17,Fteachers expressing their own views.   
OL,19,FEducation Secretary Nadhim Zahawi says 
OL,20,Fno subject should be off limits, but   
OL,21,Fteaching must be impartial.            
